title: For Sale:  Argentine  Sistema Navy  Colt 1911A1
postcontent: According to a very detailed account on the 1911 Forum :  This Sistema Colt was made in 1959. ( total production of the D.G.F.M. was 1945 to 1961 ) There were only 6,226 made for the Argentine Navy ( about 3 1/2 % of total production ) . Later pistols ordered for the Navy were Parkerized . This pistol is Parkerized. Slide is properly marked MARINA DE GUERRA ( late Navy markings ) . All numbers on the pistol match, with the exception of the magazine numbered 241 numbers earlier than the pistol. The post goes on to say that the Best available steel from Germany, Britian and Sweden were used in making them. They were made on Colt equipment , to Colt specs, and under Colt supervision. They are regarded as 100% Colt pistols. Completely made to interchange all parts with USGI parts. This pistol has had Wilson Combat sights installed front and rear, with no modification made to the slide ( original 1911A1 sights could easily be re-installed  ) Only the smallest amount of holster wear is visible at the muzzle. The lands and grooves appear to be as new. Overall condition is about 98%.  $695 ( try to buy a GI Colt for that ) FFL required outside of Oklahoma.
